This product includes a modified Arrow-to-pgwire encoder derived from the
`arrow-pg` crate in datafusion-contrib/datafusion-postgres:

  https://github.com/datafusion-contrib/datafusion-postgres

That project is licensed under the Apache License, Version 2.0. QuackGIS removes
its DataFusion and GeoArrow integration and retains the Arrow/PostgreSQL encoding
core; local divergence is documented in DIVERGENCE.md.

Runtime distributions include DuckDB and the official `spatial` and `ducklake`
extensions under their respective upstream licenses. Exact source versions and
artifact digests are recorded by the runtime manifest.

